        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 7:13PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 713 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pontiac, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Rochester around 725 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Rochester Hills,
Lakeville, Waterford, Leonard, Lake Orion, Sylvan Lake, Auburn Hills,
Lake Angelus, Keego Harbor, and Bloomfield Township.

People attending Meadow Brook Amphithreatre  should seek safe shelter
immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
